  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc6\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dda\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nihal Fonseka is reappointed to the Finance Board",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Anthony Nihal Fonseka has been reappointed as a member of the Monetary Board of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka with effect from 26 May 2022. Earlier, he served in the Monetary Board from July 2016 to May 2020.",
        "Having obtained his Bachelor of Science degree from the University of Colombo, he is a senior member of the Institute of Chartered Bankers in the United Kingdom. He is also an Honorary Fellow of the Chartered Securities and Investments Institute of the United Kingdom. He is also a Senior Independent Director and Chairman of the Group Audit Committee of John Keels Holdings Pvt. Ltd., Chairman of C/S Phoenix Industries, Non-Executive Director and Chairman of the Audit Committee of Brandix Lanka, Non-Executive Director and Chairman of the Investment Committee of C/S Phoenix Ventures. .",
        "A banker by profession, Mr. Fonseka has held several key positions in the domestic and foreign banking and finance sectors. Mr. A served as the Executive Officer of DFCC Bank for over 13 years and previously as the Deputy Chief Executive Officer of HSBC (Sri Lanka) Bank for 10 years. Mr. Fonseka has served as Chairman of the Colombo Stock Exchange and Asia Pacific Financial Development Institutions Association in Manila, and as a Director of Commercial Bank and DFCC Development Bank. He also served as the Chairman of the Sri Lanka National Advisory Council of the United Kingdom's Chartered Securities and Investment Institute for over 10 years, and is also a member of the United States - Sri Lanka Fulbright Commission.",
        "Mr. Fonseka has also held various positions in the public service. Mr. A, who was a member of the Presidential Commission on Taxation established in 2009, also served as a member of the constitutionally established National Procurement Commission. He served as a Director of the Sri Lanka Credit Information Bureau and the Employees' Trust Fund, and Co-Chairman of the Capital Markets Cluster of the National Board for Economic Development.",
        "Mr. Fonseka has authored a number of papers and delivered lectures at many local as well as foreign conferences and seminars."
      ],
